HEADWORD: Sexenary
<hw>Sex"e*na*ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Proceeding by
sixes; sextuple; -- applied especially to a system of arithmetical
computation in which the base is six.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

